  %h3 Tooltips
  %span You can display tooltips on various elements by adding a <code>rel="tooltip"</code> and <code>title</code> attribute to any element.  Here we use buttons as examples.  You can also optionally specify direction by adding a <code>data-placement</code> attribute.
  .btn-toolbar
    %button.btn{rel: 'tooltip', title: 'Tooltip in top'} Top
    %button.btn{rel: 'tooltip', title: 'Tooltip in right', data: {placement: 'right'}} Right
    %button.btn{rel: 'tooltip', title: 'Tooltip in bottom', data: {placement: 'bottom'}} Bottom
    %button.btn{rel: 'tooltip', title: 'Tooltip in left', data: {placement: 'left'}} Left


